   150→    // Giving the same flexibility via request header would require the user
   151→    // to provide HeaderMatcher serialized into a string. To avoid this extra
   152→    // complexity we only support name-only header matchers via request
   153→    // header. Anything more sophisticated needs to be provided via config.
