\n- `ManagedResourceImpl connections_` - tracks max_connections limit\n- `ManagedResourceImpl pending_requests_` - tracks max_pending_requests limit  \n- `ManagedResourceImpl requests_` - tracks max_requests limit\n- `ManagedResourceImpl retries_` - tracks max_retries with optional retry budget\n\nThe `canCreate()` method on each resource checks if the current count is below the configured maximum.\n\n### 5. HTTP Connection Pool Implementation\n\nThe HTTP-specific connection pool implementations in `source/common/http/` inherit from `ConnPoolImplBase` and `HttpConnPoolImplBase`:\n\n- `source/common/http/http1/conn_pool.cc` - HTTP/1.x connection pool\n- `source/common/http/http2/conn_pool.cc` - HTTP/2 connection pool  \n- `source/common/http/http3/conn_pool.cc` - HTTP/3 connection pool\n\nAll use the same base overflow detection logic from the parent classes.\n\n### 6. Overflow to Reset Conversion\n\nIn `source/common/router/upstream_request.cc` (lines 563-586), the `UpstreamRequest::onPoolFailure()` method converts the `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` to `StreamResetReason::Overflow`, which is then passed downstream to trigger the stream reset with the \"overflow\" reason string.\n\n### 7. Configuration Protobuf\n\nThe circuit breaker thresholds that control when overflow occurs are defined in `envoy/config/cluster/v3/circuit_breaker.proto` in the `CircuitBreakers.Thresholds` message:\n\n- `max_connections` (field 2) - default 1024: Maximum number of connections to the upstream cluster\n- `max_pending_requests` (field 3) - default 1024: Maximum number of pending requests to the upstream cluster  \n- `max_requests` (field 4) - default 1024: Maximum number of parallel requests to the upstream cluster\n- `max_retries` (field 5) - default 3: Maximum number of parallel retries to the upstream cluster\n\nWhen any of these limits are exceeded and a new stream/connection is requested, the connection pool sets the `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`, which ultimately results in a reset with \"overflow\" reason."
